    "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Nehemiah 7 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:1",
      "text": "Now after the wall was built, and I had set up the doors, and numbered the porters and singing men, and Levites:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:2",
      "text": "I commanded Hanani my brother, and Hananias ruler of the house of Jerusalem, (for he seemed as a sincere man, and one that feared God above the rest,)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:3",
      "text": "And I said to them: Let not the gates of Jerusalem be opened till the sun be hot. And while they were yet standing by the gates were shut, and barred: and I set watchmen of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, every one by their courses, and every man over against his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:4",
      "text": "And the city was very wide and great, and the people few in the midst thereof, and the houses were not built.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:5",
      "text": "But God had put in my heart, and I assembled the princes and magistrates, and common people, to number them: and I found a book of the number of them who came up at first and therein it was found written:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:6",
      "text": "These are the children of the province, who came up from the captivity of them that had been carried away, whom Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon had carried away, and who returned into Judea, every one into his own city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:7",
      "text": "Who came with Zorobabel, Josue, Nehemiah, Azarias, Raamias, Nahamani, Mardochai, Belsam, Mespharath, Begoia, Nahum, Baana. The number of the men of the people of Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:8",
      "text": "The children of Pharos, two thousand one hundred seventy-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:nehemiah.7.9",
